messages.content: Please help me monitor new paid orders in WooCommerce, retrieve the SKU and quantity of each finished product in the order, then, based on the Bill of Materials (BOM) recorded in Google Sheets, calculate the amount of raw materials that need to be consumed. Deduct the corresponding quantities from the raw material inventory table in Google Sheets, write the updated raw material inventory back to Google Sheets, and then, based on the updated raw material balances, recalculate the maximum producible quantities for all finished products. Finally, sync these maximum producible quantities to WooCommerce as the available stock for the products.

I have set up and executed the end-to-end flow for your current WooCommerce paid orders: pulled new paid orders, calculated raw material consumption from the BOM in Google Sheets, wrote back the updated material inventory, recalculated maximum producible finished goods, and synced those as available stock in WooCommerce.

What I used
- Google Spreadsheet: Raw Material Inventory Management Test
  - Sheets: BOM, Material_Inventory
- WooCommerce: Pulled orders with status processing/completed (treated as paid)

Orders processed
- Order IDs: 12, 13, 14
- Line items (SKU x Qty):
  - 12: TABLE_001 x 5, DESK_001 x 2, CHAIR_001 x 5
  - 13: CHAIR_001 x 1, TABLE_001 x 4
  - 14: CHAIR_001 x 2
- Consolidated finished goods totals:
  - CHAIR_001: 8
  - TABLE_001: 9
